# JSON Formatting Standards for Raycast AI Chat Presets

## Structure Requirements

- Use consistent indentation (2 spaces)
- Include descriptive property names
- Add comments in separate documentation files
- Validate JSON syntax before committing

## Raycast AI Chat Preset Format

- Follow Raycast's official schema for AI Chat Presets
- Include required fields: name, description, prompt
- Add optional fields: icon, keywords, author
- Use semantic versioning for preset versions
- Include metadata for categorization and search

## Best Practices

- Keep JSON files focused on a single preset
- Use descriptive file names that match the preset name
- Include example usage in documentation
- Test presets in Raycast before committing
- Document any dependencies or prerequisites

## Validation

- Ensure all required fields are present
- Validate against Raycast's schema when available
- Test JSON syntax with linter tools
- Verify preset functionality in Raycast environment
